snippet.textDisplay:
Shitty politicians are an outcome of having a shitty populace. Cream rises to the top as well as scum. 
I'd suggest avoiding extremisms - Extreme Left, Right, Religion, Athiesm or Opinion - but that is viewed as an extremist viewpoint. When I was young I was told to "learn both sides of the arguement and take the good parts from both" - the idea being that the person opposite you isn't wrong or evil or misguided, they are just trying to make sense out of a society that has no rules, but this does not work. Society was founded on the belief that "We are right" it's what'cha do with those that have a different idea of what "We are right" means. You can't get on with them properly ('cos if they arn't right, they must be wrong, right?) so what do you do? 

Here. I'll give you an example of 'Extreme Views' so you can spot it when you see it. Here goes.
"I think that war is a booster for technology and economy - if only we could go to war without actually having to hurt anyone, right? Or at least, have a war that was out of our own lands and territories.. Like... A neverending economy boosting war where we have an opponent we can't win against in a country nobody has.... waiddaminute... Korea? Vietnam? Afghanistan? What about Space Marines? Maybe we could wage war on the moon!! Not like... on the moon standing on the moon shooting lazers (like Moonraker) but more like.... Kill the Moon. It creates tides, right? And hundreds of people die each year because of... tidal stuff. If we killed the moon then there wouldn't be any tides, so less people would die."

I've gone from the basic "fact" (one given time MIGHT be proveable...) that war might boost technology and econony, added a dash of hopefullness, a bit of a self serving attitude and just let the bullshit flow. I can look back on these words and say "Yeah, I see the idea, I can't see any obvious flaws" but here is where things get tricky. Instead of next saying "I'm onto something important here, I'm going to double down!" I'm going to say "What a load of old shit I am talking. I wonder what I'll be having for lunch".

America. Go out to lunch. Take a breather. Nothing you do matters, the stars will go out eventually and the heat death of the universe is trillions upon trillions of years away. We have a lot of time in which to figure this stuff out, let's get off the planet first, 'cos there is no use in having all our eggs in one basket... No matter how big a basket-case your neibour is.
